<paragraph blockId="54.[1452,2661,274,1254]" box="[1452,1927,982,1015]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1452,1687,982,1015]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1454,2394,1022,1055]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="54.[1452,2661,274,1254]" box="[1454,2394,1022,1055]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1454,2155,1022,1055]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="538" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="54.[1452,2661,274,1254]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1454,1811,1062,1095]" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Behn’s Big-eared Bat is rarely captured. It has been recorded only in protected areas in 
<collectingCountry box="[2579,2658,1101,1134]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="538">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(e.g. Jalapao State Park).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
